[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.cli.RecursivelyExtract.main[0m[1;39m([0m[39mRecursivelyExtract.jav[0m[1;92ma:96[0m[1;39m)[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m[1;35morg.apache.tika.cli.TikaCLI.main[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaCLI.jav[0m[1;92ma:234[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppRUnpackerFuzzer.parseOne[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaAppRUnpackerFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:74[0m[1;39m)[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.TikaAppRUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTikaAppRUnpackerFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:5[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: e329145bbb375a14[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDuring a Jazzer fuzzing session against the Apache Tika RUnpack extractor, a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception was raised indicating a file path traversal[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvulnerability. The sanitizer detected that an extracted entry path contained “..[0m[35m/[0m[39m” [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msequences, attempting to escape its intended output directory and write to an [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munintended location [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`jazzer-traversal`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Observed  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A Java exception of type [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` was thrown, with the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessage “File path traversal: [0m[35m/tmp/.../input.bin/../../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal.[0m[39m” This [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates that an untrusted archive entry name allowed an attacker-controlled [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrelative path containing “..[0m[35m/[0m[39m” to traverse outside the designated output folder.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability Type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The issue is classified as a File Path Traversal vulnerability. An archive entry [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mname can cause files to be written to locations outside of the intended extraction [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdirectory.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key Findings  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The sanitizer that flagged the issue is `FilePathTraversal.check` in the Jazzer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mframework.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The problematic path originated from the Tika pipeline’s file-emitter [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomponent.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Stack trace highlights involvement of:  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `org.apache.tika.pipes.emitter.fs.FileSystemEmitter.emit`  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `org.apache.tika.pipes.extractor.EmittingEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler.add`  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – `org.apache.tika.extractor.RUnpackExtractor.storeEmbeddedBytes`  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Core parsing in `PackageParser` and higher-level parsing in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`AutoDetectParser` and `RecursiveParserWrapper`.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer entry point is `TikaAppRUnpackerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`, which [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvokes Tika’s recursive extraction routines. The harness simply feeds inputs; it [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis not the root cause of the traversal.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas to Investigate  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. File path handling in `FileSystemEmitter.emit` – how entry names are [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnormalized and combined with the target directory.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Path sanitization logic in `FilePathTraversal.checkPath` and related copy/move[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhooks.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The RUnpack extractor’s `storeEmbeddedBytes` method, which delegates to the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39memitter and may forward unsanitized paths.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Upstream archive parsing in `PackageParser.parseEntry` to understand how entry[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnames are read and passed downstream.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Any utility methods or configuration in Tika that govern safe extraction [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39me.g., path normalization, blacklist/whitelist of characters, canonicalization[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFile path traversal: [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/expander-tmp17508936857284293023/output/q/r/s/t/./input.bin/../../../[0m[95mjazzer-tr[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [95maversal[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-pipes/tika-emitters/tika-emitter-fs/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/pipes/emitte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mr/fs/FileSystemEmitter.jav[0m[1;92ma:145[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m165[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m145[0m[39m:    @Override[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m146[0m[39m:    public void [0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path, InputStream inputStream, Metadata [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muserMetadata, ParseContext parseContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException, TikaEmitterException [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:        Path target = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m148[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m149[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mFiles.isDirectory[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m150[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mFiles.createDirectories[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mtarget.getParent[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m151[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m152[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39monExists == ON_EXISTS.REPLACE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m153[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mFiles.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[39minputStream, target, [0m                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m154[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39monExists == ON_EXISTS.EXCEPTION[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m155[0m[39m:            [0m[1;35mFiles.copy[0m[1;39m([0m[39minputStream, target[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m156[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39monExists == ON_EXISTS.SKIP[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m160[0m[39m:                [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mFileAlreadyExistsException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                        [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Root-Cause Analysis**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Both overloads of `[0m[1;35mFileSystemEmitter.emit[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` directly call  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     `[0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39muserProvidedPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   without any normalization or containment check. As a result, a malicious entry [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mname containing `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m` or an absolute path can escape [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Path.resolve` on an absolute[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath yields the absolute[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, allowing writes outside the intended `basePath`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **High-Level Patch Plan**  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   Introduce a single helper method in `FileSystemEmitter` to “safe-resolve” any [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39memitter path:  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Convert the user-provided string to a `Path relative = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39muserPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Reject absolute paths: if `[0m[1;35mrelative.isAbsolute[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, throw [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaEmitterException`.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Resolve against `basePath`: `resolved = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrelative[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normalize the combined path: `resolved = [0m[1;35mresolved.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Canonicalize [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `[0m[1;35mtoAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and verify that [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mresolved.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mbasePath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. If not, throw [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TikaEmitterException` indicating a path-traversal attempt.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Return the safe, normalized `Path`.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Detailed Steps**  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `FileSystemEmitter.java`, add a private helper:  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```java[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      private Path [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString userPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws TikaEmitterException [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Reject absolute paths[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          Path relative = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39muserPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mrelative.isAbsolute[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              throw new [0m[1;35mTikaEmitterException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid absolute path: "[0m[39m + userPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Combine and normalize[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          Path combined = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrelative[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Ensure containment under basePath[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          Path normalizedBase = [0m[1;35mbasePath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mcombined.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnormalizedBase[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              throw new [0m[1;35mTikaEmitterException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"File path traversal attempt: "[0m[39m + [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muserPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return combined;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. **Refactor** the two `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods to use `[0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString emitKey, List<Metadata>[0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m old:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Path output = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m new:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Path output = [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey + [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfileExtension != null && [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mfileExtension.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m > [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m ? [0m[32m"."[0m[39m + fileExtension : [0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path, InputStream[0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m old:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Path target = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m new:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Path target = [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Preserve existing directory-creation and `onExists` logic unchanged after [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mobtaining the validated `Path`.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Justification & Preservation of Functionality**  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **No change** for well-formed, benign paths: they resolve and normalize to the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame location under `basePath`.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **All existing behaviors**—`fileExtension` appending, `ON_EXISTS` handling [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`REPLACE`, `SKIP`, `EXCEPTION`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m—remain intact.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any attempt to inject `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m` sequences or absolute paths will be caught early, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresulting in a `TikaEmitterException` instead of writing outside the emitter’s [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Side-Effects and Mitigations**  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Side-Effect**: configurations omitting `basePath` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwriting to CWD[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are still[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallowed but we enforce the same relative-path normalization.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: code documents that `basePath` is required for safe [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextraction. If `basePath` can be null in some contexts, the helper can be extended [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto handle that scenario identically [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtreating the process working directory as [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`basePath`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Testing**: add unit tests for `safeResolve`, verifying that valid relative [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpaths succeed and that `..[0m[35m/[0m[39m…` or absolute strings produce exceptions.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **No External/Harness/Test Changes**  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch touches only `FileSystemEmitter` in the core emitter module.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It does not modify fuzz harnesses, test code, or external dependencies.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing downstream logic in `EmittingEmbeddedDocumentBytesHandler`, [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`RUnpackExtractor`, and `PackageParser` remains untouched, preserving all parsing [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand embedding workflows.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. **References in Codebase**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The chosen approach aligns with canonicalization checks recommended in other [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparts of Tika where secure file writes occur [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., any future asset-fetchers[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar patterns can be retrofitted to other emitters if they share vulnerable[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mresolve[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` calls.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWith this strategy, any file-path traversal attempts are neutralized at the emitter[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundary, eliminating this critical vulnerability while retaining Tika’s rich [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39membedding and extraction functionality.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer fuzzing run against Apache Tika’s `FileSystemEmitter` triggered a          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: File path traversal` exception when an extractor      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attempted to write to a path containing “..[35m/../../[0m[95mjazzer-traversal[0m”. To mitigate, a [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patch introduced a new `[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1m([0mString[1m)[0m` helper that validates and normalizes   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         user-supplied paths before writing. After merging the patch, the build fails with a [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         compilation error in `FileSystemEmitter.java`, reporting that the local variable    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `output` is already defined in one of the `[1;35memit[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` methods.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer-generated input caused `[1;35mFileSystemEmitter.emit[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` to attempt       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         writing outside of its intended directory by passing a path containing              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         parent-directory segments [1m([0m`..`[1m)[0m.                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The framework’s `FilePathTraversal` sanitizer threw a critical exception once  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the normalized path fell outside the emitter’s base directory.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace points to                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35morg.apache.tika.pipes.emitter.fs.FileSystemEmitter.emit[0m[1m([0mFileSystemEmitter.jav[1;92ma:155[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m)[0m` as the first call in Tika code that triggers the sanitizer.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Important Observations                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The emitter logic originally used a simple `[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1m([0mkey[1m)[0m` or          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1m([0mkey[1m)[0m` without checking for absolute paths or upward directory traversal. [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Both overloads of `[1;35memit[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` in `FileSystemEmitter` [1m([0mone taking an            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `InputStream`, the other taking a `List[1m<[0m[1;95mMetadata[0m[39m>`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m share similar path-resolution [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No existing guard was present to block `..[0m[35m/../[0m[39m` sequences or absolute paths [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore filesystem writes.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a private helper:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private Path [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString userPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws TikaEmitterException [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Path relative = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39muserPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mrelative.isAbsolute[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw new [0m[1;35mTikaEmitterException[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Path root = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath != null[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 ? [0m[1;35mbasePath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 : [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Path combined = [0m[1;35mroot.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrelative[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mcombined.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throw new [0m[1;35mTikaEmitterException[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return combined;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Replaced the two original resolution blocks in each `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method with [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls to `[0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • In the `List<Metadata>` overload, substituted:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```diff[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       -   output = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m:            output = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39muserMetadata, ParseContext parseContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws IOException, TikaEmitterException [0m[1;39m{[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m147[0m[39m:        Path target = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtika-pipes/tika-emitters/tika-emitter-fs/src/main/java/org/apache/tika/pipes/emitte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mr/fs/FileSystemEmitter.jav[0m[1;92ma:140[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m144[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m140[0m[39m:    @Field[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The compilation error arises because in the metadata-list `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe local variable `output` is declared twice: once at the top [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Path output;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magain in the patched resolution line [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Path output = [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. To [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfix this, we must remove the redundant declaration and simply assign to the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting `output` variable. We will also ensure that both `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` overloads use[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for path normalization and traversal checks, preserving their [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moriginal semantics.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Detailed Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Insert `[0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` helper  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Locate the end of the `[0m[1;35msetPrettyPrint[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m143[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Immediately after it, add the private helper:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```java[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * Resolve userPath against basePath [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor CWD if basePath is null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      * normalizing and preventing traversal outside of root.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     private Path [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString userPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m throws TikaEmitterException [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Path relative = [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[39muserPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mrelative.isAbsolute[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaEmitterException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Invalid absolute path: "[0m[39m + userPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Path root = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath != null[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 ? [0m[1;35mbasePath.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 : [0m[1;35mPaths.get[0m[1;39m([0m[32m""[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.toAbsolutePath[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         Path combined = [0m[1;35mroot.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrelative[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.normalize[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mcombined.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mroot[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             throw new [0m[1;35mTikaEmitterException[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"File path traversal attempt: "[0m[39m + [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muserPath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return combined;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This centralizes path validation for both `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Patch metadata-list overload  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `public void [0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString emitKey, List<Metadata> metadataList, ParseContext[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparseContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Remove lines [0m[1;36m86[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m90[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbasePath != null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Replace them with:[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        output = [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39memitKey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. This assignment uses the existing `Path output;` declared at line [0m[1;36m78[0m[39m, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoiding a redeclaration.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Patch InputStream overload  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `public void [0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString path, InputStream inputStream, Metadata [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muserMetadata, ParseContext parseContext[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Change the resolution line from:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Path target = [0m[1;35mbasePath.resolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        to[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        Path target = [0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. This ensures the same traversal checks for streamed emits.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We keep the original writer/copy semantics, directory-creation logic, and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`onExists` policies unchanged.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `fileExtension` logic in the metadata-list overload remains intact.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The helper does not alter behavior when `emitKey` or `path` is well-formed; it[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly rejects absolute or traversal paths.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness tests or fuzzing logic are modified.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing tests and consumers of `FileSystemEmitter` continue to function [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas before for valid paths.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Should any other emitter classes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnon-filesystem[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m require similar guards, they[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan adopt `[0m[1;35msafeResolve[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`—but this patch scope is limited to [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FileSystemEmitter`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. References  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Follows patterns from other secure path-resolution code in Tika [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., where [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mZIP extraction sanitizes entry names[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensures consistency between both `[0m[1;35memit[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` overloads.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fixes the compilation error by removing the duplicate `output` declaration.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
